I"«<p>Do you have a software in your laptop or desktop that is making your pc heat up really fast?</p>

<p>Well in this tutorial I will show you how you can uninstall the software or application through the control panel.</p>

<h3 id="step-1-open-the-control-panel-from-the-windows-search-bar">STEP 1: Open the control panel from the windows search bar</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Click on the window key or Move your mouse to the windows icon and click on it</li>
  <li>Search for <code>control panel</code></li>
  <li>Control panel will appear below the windows bar.</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="../assets/images/step1a.jpg" alt="Step 1" /></p>

<h3 id="step-2-click-on-the-control-panel">STEP 2: Click on the ‚ÄúCONTROL PANEL‚Äù</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Click on it to open.</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="../assets/images/step2.jpg" alt="step 2" /></p>

<h3 id="step-3-click-on-uninstall-a-program-under-programs">STEP 3: Click on ‚ÄúUninstall a program‚Äù under Programs.</h3>

<p><img src="../assets/images/step3.jpg" alt="step 3" /></p>

<h3 id="step-4-search-for-the-software-you-want-to-uninstall">STEP 4: Search for the software you want to uninstall</h3>
<ul>
  <li>If software name is not on first screen, stroll down to search for it</li>
  <li>If found, right click on the Software/Application</li>
  <li>Uninstall or Repair will appear, click on Uninstall.</li>
</ul>

<p><img src="../assets/images/step4.jpg" alt="step 4a" />
<img src="../assets/images/step4b.jpg" alt="ste4b" /></p>

<h3 id="step-5-click-on-uninstall-from-the-windows-opened">STEP 5: Click on uninstall from the windows opened</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>The uninstall tab is not the same for all softwares</p>
</blockquote>

